<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12">
    <div class="clearfix">
      <p class="float-right">
        <%= link_to "Log in", new_session_path('user'), class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
        <%= link_to "Sign up", new_registration_path('user'), class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class='row'>
  <div class='offset-sm-2 col-sm-8 col-12'>
    <div class='jumbotron'>
      <h1 class='display-4'>
        Welcome to MyApp
      </h1>
      <p class='lead'>
      </p>
      <hr class='mt-4'>
      <p>
        Start using the app by signing up as a user (tenant).
      </p>
      <p>
        When you are signing up you are asked for a subdomain. This will be your own subdomain. Everything belonging to your user will be accessible only via this subdomain. Actually in this app it’s only a fake dashboard which belongs to a user. But nevertheless it’s only reachable via a subdomain.
      </p>
      <p>
        After logging in try to access your dashboard through another subdomain even a subdomain which belongs to another user and see what happens.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
